<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy - Pitch///asters</title>

  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fjalla+One&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include("./partials/header") %>

  <main class="container py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-muted mb-4">Last updated: <span id="last-updated">April 1, 2026</span></p>

        <div class="privacy-content">
          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>Welcome to Pitch///asters ("we", "our", or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our platform.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <h3>2.1 Account Information</h3>
            <p>When you sign in via GitHub, we collect:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Your GitHub username</li>
              <li>Your display name</li>
              <li>Your GitHub profile picture URL</li>
              <li>Your GitHub user ID</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Project Information</h3>
            <p>When you create or import projects, we store:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Project titles and descriptions</li>
              <li>Project stories and documentation</li>
              <li>Links to GitHub repositories, websites, and videos</li>
              <li>Project cover images</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.3 Usage Data</h3>
            <p>We automatically collect information about how you interact with our platform, including:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Pages you visit</li>
              <li>Actions you take (such as attending hackathons, submitting responses)</li>
              <li>Timestamps of your activities</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services</li>
              <li>Display your projects and profile to other users</li>
              <li>Facilitate feedback and collaboration on hackathon projects</li>
              <li>Send you notifications about activities related to your projects</li>
              <li>Understand how users interact with our platform</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>4. Information Sharing</h2>
            <p>Your public profile and projects are visible to other users and visitors. This includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Your username and display name</li>
              <li>Your projects and their descriptions</li>
              <li>Your participation in hackathons and events</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <p>We store your data in SQLite databases on secure servers. While we implement reasonable security measures, please understand that no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Access your personal information</li>
              <li>Delete your account and associated data</li>
              <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise these rights, you can delete your account from the Settings page or contact us.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
            <p>We use session cookies to maintain your login state and provide a seamless experience. These cookies are essential for the platform to function properly.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>Our platform integrates with third-party services:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>GitHub</strong> - For user authentication</li>
              <li><strong>Devpost</strong> - For importing project information</li>
              <li><strong>Luma</strong> - For importing hackathon event information</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These services have their own privacy policies which govern their data practices.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Our service is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify users of any material changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
            <p>
              <a href="https://day50.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">day50.dev</a>
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include("./partials/footer") %>
</body>
</html>
